{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1124cfc6-d589-46e8-87bd-8dada8ffa19f","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nIf you need to specify the project:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so `FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests` matches any test whose fully qualified name includes that string.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c0f233c6-8476-4be7-b358-a2a123bdba94","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question about the dotnet CLI - I can answer directly without needing to look at files.","outputTokens":196,"requestId":"BD09:3F44A7:21FCA6D:2699BF3:6A07E09F"},"id":"b6b18dd7-a504-4491-8d2e-a4ae1b1ba1fb","timestamp":"2026-05-16T03:12:37.497Z","parentId":"ea7fc842-d2a7-4855-b07f-8ff0bb8807f8"}
